From 382b5d3fe034c3f11e5c05fea70b0ed0e3053fe7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: YTing46 <q36141367@gs.ncku.edu.tw>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 20:42:22 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 03/23] riscv: dts: sg2002: set Duo256M USB to peripheral for
 ADB gadget

The Duo256M's DWC2 controller is dual-role capable, but the ADB-over-USB
bring-up (functionfs adbd + configfs gadget) needs it enumerated as a USB
peripheral so a host PC can see the board. Switch dr_mode from "host" to
"peripheral"; a UDC (4340000.usb) now appears under /sys/class/udc and the
host `adb devices` lists the board.

---
 arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts
index 3681a32a1472..da85547dfd17 100644
--- a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts
+++ b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts
@@ -127,6 +127,6 @@ &uart0 {
 };
 
 &usb {
-	dr_mode = "host";
+	dr_mode = "peripheral";
 	status = "okay";
 };
-- 
2.34.1

